title:
History of the U.S.S. Leviathan, cruiser and transport forces, United States Atlantic fleet
Compiled from the ship's log and data gathered by the history committee on board the ship
author: U.S.S. Leviathan History Committee

quoteLast: on a summer night. And if only I felt a bit hungry this is what I should wish--spread out on a damask cloth before me in a few gold-medallioned Chinese dishes, with no forks or knives: first of all, two thin _foie-gras_ sandwiches, four grilled snails and maybe a little alligator pear: on top of those, two truffles: on top of those, two slim onions: on top of those, two thin salted biscuits: on top of those, a bit of Camembert cheese: on top of that, two cigarettes: on top of all a hollow-stemmed glass of sparkling Burgundy.
title: I, Mary MacLane: A Diary of Human Days
author: MacLane, Mary, 1881-1929
